      "block_type": "flowchart",
      "title": "Inhibitor switch circuit check",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "n1",
          "type": "action",
          "text": "Check input signal\n1. Switch ignition to \"ON\"\n2. Select \"DATA MONITOR\"\n   \u2022 Check that reading changes from \"OFF\" to \"ON\" when selector lever is moved from P, R, N, D and Ds position in this order\n\u2014 OR \u2014\n   \u2022 Check voltage between the N-CVT control unit terminals #5, #10, #2, #3 and ground while moving selector lever through each range.\n   Voltage between terminals and ground:\n   B = Battery voltage\n   0 = 0V\n   [Table: see voltage_table block]"
        },
        {
          "id": "n2",
          "type": "decision",
          "text": "O.K. / N.G."
        },
        {
          "id": "n3",
          "type": "action",
          "text": "Check following items:\n\u2022 Inhibitor switch (refer to \"Electrical component inspection\")\n\u2022 Harness continuity between ignition switch and inhibitor switch\n\u2022 Harness continuity between inhibitor switch and N-CVT control unit"
        },
        {
          "id": "n4",
          "type": "action",
          "text": "Perform self diagnosis after test drive"
        },
        {
          "id": "n5",
          "type": "decision",
          "text": "O.K. / N.G."
        },
        {
          "id": "n6",
          "type": "action",
          "text": "1. Check N-CVT control unit I/O signal\n2. Re-check N-CVT control unit pin terminals for damage or incorrect connection of control unit harness connector"
        },
        {
          "id": "n7",
          "type": "terminal",
          "text": "Inspection end"
        }
      ],
